@X fusion_attn_dsweep_pipe := "R11 head_dim sweep + 2-stage compute-pipeline of R10's multi-warp+cp.async fused FlashAttention — BOTH pre-registered levers FALSIFIED. (A) the fused/cuBLAS-TC ratio WORSENS monotonically with d (d64 ~1.23x -> d128 ~1.75x -> d256 ~2.22x): cuBLAS is dominated by the d-INDEPENDENT N*N S HBM round-trip so it barely slows with d, while the fused per-warp serial d-tile loop scales LINEARLY with d — raising head_dim WIDENS the gap, opposite the hypothesis. (B) software-pipelining the COMPUTE (hoist QK^T(j+1) over P.V(j), race-free triple-buffer) is +2.4..4.9% SLOWER than R10 — the dependency chain is NOT an exposed bubble (4 warps * 20 warps/SM already interleave the wmma streams). Campaign-best ratio stays R10's 1.149x @ N=4096 d=64; NEAR-CEILING closed-negative ruling out the d and compute-overlap levers for fused attention at d∈{64..256}." :: discovery [slug=fusion-attention-dsweep-pipe group=GPU]
  seed         = "F-FUSION-ATTN-DSWEEP-PIPE — (A) re-run R10 at d∈{64,128,256}, N∈{1024,2048,4096}: hypothesis that d≥128 raises fused inner-GEMM arithmetic intensity and crosses ≤1.0x above cuBLAS-stack; (B) 2-stage compute pipeline overlapping P.V(j) with QK^T(j+1) at best-d to break the intra-warp dependency chain R10 found is the floor. WIN = fused_ms < cublas_stack_ms on ≥1 shape."
  date         = "2026-05-26"
  host         = "ubu-2 RTX 5070 sm_120 driver 580 (48 SMs, 0% util at every fire)"
  verdict_tier_target  = "GREEN above-cuBLAS-stack (≤1.0x cross) OR ORANGE near-ceiling closed-negative (measured)"
  verdict_tier_reached = "ORANGE near-ceiling closed-negative (WIN clause RED-falsified on every shape; BOTH levers ruled out)"

  finding_1    = "BASELINE INTEGRITY (caught before any claim): the fused kernel is FP16-TC; a `cublas_probe` launch-decomposition showed a NAIVE one-thread-per-row softmax was a 13x-slower STRAWMAN (softmax alone 2.154 ms @ N=4096 vs the two GEMMs' 0.316 ms). A 🟢 against that strawman would have been DISHONEST — REJECTED. Fixed to an OPTIMIZED block-per-row parallel-reduction softmax; corrected cuBLAS-TC stack = 0.176 ms @ N=4096 d=64, matching R10's recorded 0.189 ms baseline ballpark. ALL ratios use the fair baseline."
  finding_2    = "NUMERIC PASS all 12 measured shapes (9 probe-A + 3 probe-B), naninf=0, per-row-scaled rel 5.6-7.1e-4. d=64 rows bit-identical to R10 (faithful parameterization). ptxas-clean 0-spill: fa_dsweep 91/148/247 reg (sm_80) @ d=64/128/256, smem 14336/22528/38912 B all << 49152 cap; fa_pipe 104 reg / 18432 B."
  finding_3    = "PROBE (A) d-sweep FALSIFIED IN THE WRONG DIRECTION. ratio fused/cuBLAS-TC: d=64 {1.229,1.225,1.234} d=128 {2.149,1.673,1.752} d=256 {2.967,2.290,2.217} @ N={1024,2048,4096}. The ratio WORSENS monotonically with d at every N. ROOT CAUSE: cuBLAS's two big TC GEMMs are bottlenecked by the d-INDEPENDENT N*N S-matrix HBM round-trip (cuBLAS @ N=4096: 0.176/0.233/0.354 ms barely rises with d); the fused per-warp serial d-tile loop (DTILES=d/16 mma + scale_o + P-repack on the critical chain) scales LINEARLY with d (fused @ N=4096: 0.217/0.409/0.786 ms). Raising head_dim WIDENS the gap. The d-lever is RULED OUT — the d-trend DIVERGES from a crossover, no extrapolation reaches ≤1.0x."
  finding_4    = "PROBE (B) compute-pipeline FALSIFIED at best-d (d=64). v1 (hoist QK^T but serialize the load) = +18.9..27.9% slower — confirms R10's cp.async LOAD-overlap is the dominant lever, do NOT trade it away. v2 (race-free triple-buffer K+V: keep 2-deep load overlap AND hoist QK^T(j+1) from the prefetched slot, numeric bit-identical) = +4.9/+4.2/+2.4% SLOWER than R10 @ N=1024/2048/4096. The intra-warp QK^T->reduce->P.V chain is NOT an exposed pipeline bubble: with 4 warps * 20 warps/SM the scheduler already interleaves the independent wmma streams; the hoist adds a __syncthreads + register pressure (93->104) that costs more than it saves."
  finding_5    = "CAMPAIGN-BEST ratio remains R10's 1.149x @ N=4096 d=64 (probe-B did not beat it; R11 probe-A measured d=64 ~1.23x vs the fair cuBLAS-TC baseline this session, within run-to-run variance). The fused-attention fusable axis is NEAR-CEILING at d∈{64..256}: it approaches cuBLAS within ~23% at the favorable d=64 but the inner-GEMM TC-utilization gap is FUNDAMENTAL — both of the two most-plausible remaining levers (deeper d, compute-overlap) move the wrong way or don't help."

  binding      = "the fused attention floor at d∈{64..256} is set by (1) cuBLAS's single-launch big-GEMM TC pipeline utilization that the 16x16-tile fused inner GEMMs cannot match, and (2) cuBLAS being bottlenecked on the d-independent N*N S HBM round-trip so it does NOT pay the per-d cost the fused path does. Neither raising d nor software-pipelining the compute crosses it."
  win          = "NO — fused 1.225-2.967x cuBLAS-TC across the sweep, NEVER ≤1.0x. Axis-A attention still NOT-above-cuBLAS. GPU.md §10 box UNCHANGED. No paper (orange)."

  next_cycle   = "(a) wgmma (sm_90 async warpgroup mma m64nNk16) instead of legacy 16x16 wmma — the ONE lever NOT yet tried that directly attacks finding-3/5's TC-utilization gap (bigger per-instruction tile -> higher arithmetic intensity per issue); needs sm_90 native (RTX 5070 driver-JITs from compute_90). (b) FP8 inputs (e4m3) on the Blackwell TCs to double TC throughput. (c) accept the d∈{64..256} fused-attention axis as a measured NEAR-CEILING closed-negative and pivot the fusable-axis @goal to a DIFFERENT op-pair where cuBLAS truly forces an HBM round-trip the fused kernel removes AND the fused inner-GEMM can saturate TCs (e.g. larger-tile GEMM+epilogue, not attention). Do NOT re-sweep d (ruled out) and do NOT re-try compute-pipelining at d=64 (ruled out)."

  artifacts    = "archive/fires/fusion_attn_dsweep_pipe_2026_05_26/ : fa_dsweep_oracle.cu (probe-A d-parameterized kernel DTILES=D/16), fa_pipe_oracle.cu (probe-B triple-buffer compute-pipeline), fusion_attn_cublas_tc_baseline.cu (fair FP16 cuBLAS-TC stack w/ OPTIMIZED parallel softmax), cublas_probe.cu (launch-decomposition that caught the naive-softmax strawman), result_probeA.json + result_probeB.json (full matrices). Base = R10 fa_mw_cpasync_oracle.cu."
  verdict      = ".verdicts/fusion-attention-dsweep-pipe/F-FUSION-ATTN-DSWEEP-PIPE.txt"
